common_pitfalls:
  - "Skipping decision-gate verification collapses the playbook into a checklist"
  - "Treating outputs as optional kills traceability and future re-use"
  - "Running stages out of order because one feels more urgent absorbs risk downstream"

quality_checklist:
  - "Did every stage produce a written artifact a stranger could read?"
  - "Did I advance only when the decision-gate criterion was met in writing?"
  - "Did I document every methodology gap before it shipped to a user?"

